Attention Clara Peterson Pre-School students!
We will host a Pre-School Back to School Night this Tuesday, August 18. We ask that girls attending preschool visit us from 5:00-5:45 pm and boys attending preschool visit us from 6:00-6:45. Each student may bring one adult as well as school
supplies to the Back-to-School Night.

Please wear a face mask and practice social distancing during your visit. You may enter Clara Pete at the old north entrance, and exit through the west Park Street entrance. If you have any questions please contact the Clara Peterson office at 379-2531. We look forward to seeing our Pre-School students Tuesday evening!

Kindergarten Backpack Night Thursday, August 13

Attention Kindergarten parents-
In order to allow more time to finalize class lists, we will be holding ALL Kindergarten Backpack nights on Thursday, August 13. This is a change from our previous plans.
The schedule will be as follows:
Mrs. Jones 5:00-5:45-Boys 6:15-7:00-Girls
Mrs. Gooden 5:00-5:45-Boys 6:15-7:00-Girls
Mrs. Talbert 5:15-6:00-Boys 6:30-7:15-Girls
Mrs. Peden 5:15-6:00-Boys 6:30-7:15-Girls
Miss Harrison 5:30-6:15-Boys 6:45-7:30-Girls

We will be releasing teacher assignments and more information to all Clara Peterson students early next week. Please remember only one adult with each kindergarten student, we ask that you wear a mask and we will be practicing social distancing during this event. Please call the Clara Peterson office with any questions. We look forward to meeting all of our new Kindergarten students!

post_text:
The following are medical requirements for students attending Clara Peterson in the fall

Preschool Students:
● Physical Exam (Parents must complete the yes/no questions on the back and sign and date)
● Complete immunization record signed by a doctor: (4) DTap, (3)Polio, (4)Hib, (3)Hep B, (1)MMR,(1)Varicella, (4)Pneumococcal

Kindergarten Students:
● Physical Exam (Parents must complete the yes/no questions on the back and sign and date)
● Complete immunization record signed by a doctor: (5)DTap, (4)Polio, (4)Hib, (3)Hep B, (2)MMR, (2)Varicella, (4)Pneumococcal
● Dental Exam on IL form due May 15, 2021 (dated within 18 months of May 15th deadline)
● Eye Exam on Illinois form dated within one year of the first day of school

Second Grade Students:
● Dental Exam on IL form due May 15, 2021 (dated within 18 months of May 15th deadline)

Please call the CP office at 379-9910 with any questions.

post_text: The PBL Community and the PBL Backpack Program can not say thank you enough for the support of the Stagen family and all the families that participated in the Front Porch Project! What an amazing contribution to the students and families of Paxton Buckley Loda 💙💛 #pantherproud💛💙 Yet another great day to be a Panther!
shared_text:
YOUTUBE.COM
Front Porch Project

Julie Stagen
April 23 at 3:38 PM · YouTube ·

To say the Front Porch Project was a success is an understatement. For the past two weeks, Haley Stagen and I have been driving around snapping pictures of families outside of their homes. Some were funny, some were serious, but ALL were appreciated. We cannot say THANK YOU enough to everyone who participated. By allowing us to come to your home and take photos of your family, you were a part of something big for our community.

We started this project hoping to get 15-20 families involved and raise a few bucks for a great program. By the end, we had visited over 70 families (while keeping our distance), met so many wonderful people, and raised $2,500 for the PBL Backpack Program. Thank you from the bottom of our hearts for making this such a cool project to be a part of! Enjoy this short slideshow of the wonderful people involved.

- Julie & Haley

Clara Peterson Parents,
If you drop off your student in the morning, and/ or pick up your student in the afternoon, please do not drop off or pick up on Franklin Street. Please use the drop off and pick up lane on the south side of Clara Peterson. This is for the safety of all students.
Also, cars are not permitted in the bus lane before 8:30 am, or after 2:30 pm.
Thank you for your cooperation in this safety matter for our students.

post_text: Way to go Clara Peterson students and families!!
shared_text:
Amy Swan is with Michele Brian Cosgrove and 2 others.
February 28 at 9:59 PM ·

What a FUN night last night and assembly today! Thank you to everyone who helped in some way! So many to name!

Heart Healthy Night was a huge success because of all the awesome volunteers! Our community is awesome! And amazing high school students took time out of their Thursday night to hang out with us! So cool!

We gave away tons of prizes thanks to all the businesses in town who donated!

The kids found out Coldwell Banker Realty (Brooke M. and Kennedy W.) paid for the Paxton True Value bounce house for the WHOLE SCHOOL all day Wednesday as a reward for us reaching our goal! Woot woot!

Finally, these two got to throw pies in Barry and Amanda Styck face today! So happy I work with awesome people willing to do anything for the kids!

Katie Grice Peggy Popel Seibring Kasha Marie Wendy Niebuhr Donna Howe Brooke Mullins Kennedy Witheft Christopher Wayne Lindsay Frichtl Carla Cole Latimer Scott Allen Julie Wheaton Foster Justin Swan

post_text: September is Attendance Awareness Month. Did you know that a student is considered chronically absent if they miss 10% or more of the school year, excused or unexcused? This averages out to only 2 days per month! Chronic absenteeism can put students at greater risk of academic failure. We realize there are sometimes barriers that families face which can make regular attendance difficult. PBL wants to partner with our families to help our students to achieve regular attendance. Contact the school office if we can help!

February 12, 2019 at 10:06 PM ·

Attention parents of incoming PBL kindergarteners, Clara Peterson’s kindergarten screening and pre-registration will be Wednesday, February 20th from 8:30-11 and 1:00-6:00, and Monday, February 25th from 8:30-11 and 1:00-3:00. Please call the Clara Peterson office between 9:00 and 3:45 at 217-379-2531 to schedule an appointment for your child for one of those days.

If your child attends preschool AT Clara Peterson there is no need to make an appointment, we will screen your child while they are at school.

The screening of your child will take no more than 30 minutes and you can fill out registration paperwork while you wait. You can also bring your child’s birth certificate and physical/eye exam/dental appointment paperwork if your child has already been.

Thank you!! Please share! The kindergarten teachers are excited to meet our new batch of kiddos!!
